WEBVTT

00:10:29.411 --> 00:10:32.957
AG: And I think there was a little bit
of "Woo" -- winning over others --

00:10:32.981 --> 00:10:34.258
loaded with that as well.

00:10:34.584 --> 00:10:35.750
MB: Yeah. "Command."

00:10:35.774 --> 00:10:38.774
AG: Yeah, so I sort of
took this as feedback

00:10:38.798 --> 00:10:42.258
and said, OK, this is probably
going to be a useful skill as a teacher.

00:10:42.965 --> 00:10:47.815
And a few years ago, I had a student
who called me for some career advice.

00:10:47.839 --> 00:10:49.463
And I gave her a bunch of advice,

00:10:49.487 --> 00:10:53.065
and at the end of the conversation,
she said, "You're a logic bully."

00:10:54.347 --> 00:10:55.688
MB: You're a logic bully?

00:10:55.712 --> 00:10:57.974
AG: Yeah, and I was like,
"What does that mean?"

00:10:57.998 --> 00:11:00.991
And she said, "You just overwhelmed me
with rational arguments,